  "text": "The induction of the QDE-2 protein by dsRNA was rapid: it was observed 1 h after dsRNA production began and peaked after 8 h (Fig. 2B) . On the other hand, DCL-2 accumulated with slower kinetics (Fig. 3B) . A 6-h dsRNA induction led to only a modest activation of dcl-2 expression (Fig. 3B) . These data suggest that dsRNA differentially regulates these two genes. qde-2 is likely to be an immediate target of the dsRNA VOL. [CITATION_1] 2007 DOUBLE-STRANDED RNA INDUCED RNAi 4003 regulatory pathway, and a secondary response leads to the activation of dcl-2. Physiological function of the RNAi pathway activated by dsRNA. As we have shown in this study, the induction of QDE-2 (and probably other RNAi components) is required for efficient RNAi in Neurospora (Fig. 4) . These data suggest that the induction of QDE-2 and DCL-2 is a regulatory mechanism that can significantly increase the efficiency of the RNAi pathway and, therefore, the removal of dsRNA. The removal of dsRNA is achieved by two mechanisms. First, dsRNA is detected by DCLs and is cleaved into siRNA. Second, guided by siRNA, QDE-2 along with other components of the RISC complex will lead to the destruction of RNA template for the production of dsRNA.",
